   FDA logo U.S. Food and Drug Administration
   Center for Food Safety & Applied Nutrition

                           NOTICE!-NOTICE!-NOTICE!
          WORLD CLASS PROFESSIONALS ARE CURRENTLY BEING RECRUITED!

   The FDA/ Center for Food Safety and Applied Nutrition (CFSAN) is
   recruiting positions such as consumer safety officers, microbiologists,
   toxicologists, chemists, biologists, pharmacists, physical scientists,
   food technologists, and administrative support staff, to name a few.
   Basic requirements for this position can be obtain by requesting a copy
   of the vacancy announcement in which you are interested in applying
   for.

   Salary Range: Civil service GS-7 through GS-15 is $28,866 - $110,028
   per annum, plus an excellent benefits package and flexible work
   schedule. Salary, benefits and levels of responsibility are
   commensurate with education and experience. Positions may also be
   filled by appointment in the U.S. Public Health Service, Commissioned
   Corps with commensurate salary and benefits.

   How to Apply: For employment information, visit our websites at
   http://www.fda.gov (click on Index and Job Openings), or
   http://www.fda.gov/ohrms/vacancy/jobs.htm. You may also visit the
   Office of Personnel Management website at
   http://www.usajobs.opm.gov/a9fda.htm. Candidates should follow the
   instructions of the announcements very carefully to ensure full
   consideration.
